    },
    {
      "id": "intro_2",
      "role": "Narrator",
      "text": "The hovercraft",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 2.96,
      "endTime": 10.3
    },
    {
      "id": "intro_3",
      "role": "Narrator",
      "text": "What is a hovercraft riding on when it is in motion?",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 10.31,
      "endTime": 16.54,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "What",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "什么"
          },
          {
            "word": "Is",
            "pos": "v.",
            "meaning": "是"
          },
          {
            "word": "It",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "它"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "intro_4",
      "role": "Narrator",
      "text": "Many strange new means of transport have been developed in our century,",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 16.55,
      "endTime": 22.28,
      "analysis": {
        "words": []
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s1",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "the strangest of them being perhaps the hovercraft.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 22.29,
      "endTime": 27.28
    },
    {
      "id": "s2",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "In 1953, a former electronics engineer in his fifties, Christopher Cockerell,",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 27.29,
      "endTime": 35.43,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "Engineer",
            "pos": "n.",
            "meaning": "工程师"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s3",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "who had turned to boat-building on the Norfolk Broads,",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 35.44,
      "endTime": 39.51
    },
    {
      "id": "s4",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "suggested an idea on which he had been working for many years to the British Government and industrial circles.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 39.52,
      "endTime": 48.12
    },
    {
      "id": "s5",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "It was the idea of supporting a craft on a 'pad', or cushion, of low-pressure air, ringed with a curtain of higher pressure air.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 48.13,
      "endTime": 60.19,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "It",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "它"
          },
          {
            "word": "Air",
            "pos": "n.",
            "meaning": "空格"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s6",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "Ever since, people have had difficulty in deciding whether the craft should be ranged among ships, planes,",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 60.2,
      "endTime": 69.37,
      "analysis": {
        "words": []
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s7",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "or land vehicles--for it is something in between a boat and an aircraft.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 69.38,
      "endTime": 77.56,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "It",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "它"
          },
          {
            "word": "Is",
            "pos": "v.",
            "meaning": "是"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s8",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "As a shipbuilder, Cockerell was trying to find a solution to the problem of the wave resistance which wastes a good deal of a surface ship's power and limits its speed.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 77.57,
      "endTime": 91.53,
      "analysis": {
        "words": []
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s9",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "His answer was to lift the vessel out of the water by making it ride on a cushion of air, no more than one or two feet thick.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 91.54,
      "endTime": 102.59,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "It",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "它"
          },
          {
            "word": "Air",
            "pos": "n.",
            "meaning": "空格"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s10",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "This is done by a great number of ring-shaped air jets on the bottom of the craft.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 102.6,
      "endTime": 109.59,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "This",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "这，这个"
          },
          {
            "word": "Is",
            "pos": "v.",
            "meaning": "是"
          },
          {
            "word": "Number",
            "pos": "n.",
            "meaning": "号码，数字"
          },
          {
            "word": "Air",
            "pos": "n.",
            "meaning": "空格"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s11",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "It 'flies', therefore, but it cannot fly higher--its action depends on the surface, water or ground, over which it rides.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 109.6,
      "endTime": 122.28,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "It",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "它"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s12",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "The first tests on the Solent in 1959 caused a sensation.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 122.29,
      "endTime": 128.56
    },
    {
      "id": "s13",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "The hovercraft travelled first over the water, then mounted the beach, climbed up the dunes, and sat down on a road.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 128.57,
      "endTime": 139.56
    },
    {
      "id": "s14",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "Later it crossed the Channel, riding smoothly over the waves, which presented no problem.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 139.57,
      "endTime": 148.88,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "It",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "它"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s15",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "Since that time, various types of hovercraft have appeared and taken up regular service.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 148.89,
      "endTime": 156.3,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "That",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "那个"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s16",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "The hovercraft is particularly useful in large areas with poor communications such as Africa or Australia;",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 156.31,
      "endTime": 164.81,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "Is",
            "pos": "v.",
            "meaning": "是"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s17",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "it can become a 'flying fruit-bowl', carrying bananas from the plantations to the ports;",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 164.82,
      "endTime": 171.88,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "It",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "它"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s18",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "giant hovercraft liners could span the Atlantic;",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 171.89,
      "endTime": 175.66
    },
    {
      "id": "s19",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "and the railway of the future may well be the 'hovertrain',",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 175.67,
      "endTime": 179.98,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "Well",
            "pos": "adj.",
            "meaning": "健康的，良好的"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s20",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "riding on its air cushion over a single rail, which it never touches, at speeds, up to 300 m.p.h.--the possibilities appear unlimited.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 179.99,
      "endTime": 184.99,
      "analysis": {
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "Air",
            "pos": "n.",
            "meaning": "空格"
          },
          {
            "word": "It",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "它"
          },
          {
            "word": "At",
            "pos": "prep.",
            "meaning": "在...（小地点/时刻）"
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ]
